WEBVTT

00:12.721 --> 00:15.306
My name is Kyung-ja Kim.

00:16.016 --> 00:17.225
Oh-nam Ju's mother,

00:17.892 --> 00:18.935
Kyung-ja Kim.

01:54.739 --> 02:00.620
MASK GIRL

02:01.287 --> 02:04.457
KYUNG-JA KIM

02:06.334 --> 02:07.836
I grew up with nothing.

02:08.419 --> 02:10.713
So I've always thought
dating was a luxury.

02:11.756 --> 02:13.675
I met my husband through a matchmaker.

02:14.801 --> 02:17.887
I didn't care about looks.
That never mattered to me.

02:18.930 --> 02:20.723
He told me he had a steady job,

02:20.807 --> 02:22.934
and that was enough for me to marry him.

02:24.102 --> 02:26.312
Plus, he didn't seem
like the type to have an affair.

02:27.856 --> 02:30.191
But even though he barely made any money,

02:30.275 --> 02:32.610
that fucking bastard
shacked up with some bitch

02:32.694 --> 02:34.070
right after we got married.

02:34.779 --> 02:38.074
So, after just three years,
our marriage came to an end.

02:40.243 --> 02:41.327
But do you know what?

02:42.036 --> 02:43.121
I was okay.

02:43.830 --> 02:45.957
Because I had my son, Oh-nam.

02:46.624 --> 02:50.003
I could do everything and anything
because I had him.

03:02.390 --> 03:03.808
Stand closer to the urinals.

03:04.434 --> 03:05.560
Don't miss, y'all.

03:12.317 --> 03:13.276
Hold it in.

03:13.359 --> 03:15.778
H-- Hold it in, hold it in, hold it in!
Get out!

03:15.862 --> 03:18.031
Out, out, out, get out, come on.

03:19.532 --> 03:20.450
Ugh.

03:21.117 --> 03:22.785
What did you eat, buddy? Damn.

03:22.869 --> 03:24.370
Sighs.

03:24.454 --> 03:26.664
After working my fingers to the bone,

03:26.748 --> 03:29.209
I was finally able
to open a small restaurant.

03:29.292 --> 03:31.419
I have seats available,
this way, c'mon, let's go.

03:31.502 --> 03:34.464
Cheonggukjang? Sure, I can make that.
Whatever, you name it.

03:34.547 --> 03:38.801
Hey! Hey! Hey you! Wait-- You think you're
the only one running a business here?

03:38.885 --> 03:40.595
You just took the custom--

03:40.678 --> 03:42.513
-I didn't drag them here, did I?
-Yeah, but--

03:42.597 --> 03:44.474
If they don't like your food,
they eat mine.

03:44.557 --> 03:46.976
If they don't like my food,
they can eat yours.

03:47.060 --> 03:49.646
-So stop bitching about it for a second.
-How dare--

03:49.729 --> 03:51.773
-Just a minute--
-You bitch!

03:51.856 --> 03:55.568
I had no choice but to be like that,
so that I could put food on the table

03:55.652 --> 03:57.070
and raise my child properly.

03:57.153 --> 03:59.280
-Get off me!
-Hey, stop!

04:00.531 --> 04:03.076
-Get your dirty hands off me!
-Ow! Let go!

04:03.159 --> 04:05.370
But raising a kid
was harder than I thought.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.748
When Oh-nam was little,

04:08.831 --> 04:10.667
some of his things would go missing.

04:10.750 --> 04:14.087
What do you mean, you lost it?
No way. I bought it two days ago.

04:14.587 --> 04:16.881
He would sometimes come home with bruises.

04:16.965 --> 04:18.007
What happened here?

04:18.716 --> 04:20.301
I fell when I was playing.

04:20.385 --> 04:22.929
Why are you
so clumsy and careless?

04:23.012 --> 04:25.640
He even came home
with gum in his hair one day.

04:25.723 --> 04:26.849
Oh my-- What is this?

04:26.933 --> 04:29.852
I don't even know
when it got stuck there.

04:29.936 --> 04:32.772
Oh my goodness. Come with me!

04:32.855 --> 04:34.274
Whenever something happened,

04:34.357 --> 04:37.443
I would think, "Maybe I'm not
taking care of him well enough."

04:37.527 --> 04:40.613
Even in pitch darkness,
may he learn to hear your voice!

04:40.697 --> 04:41.864
Amen, Lord.

04:41.948 --> 04:45.952
Oh Lord, may you be the light
that guides him through his sorrow.

04:46.035 --> 04:47.495
Under your authority, Lord,

04:47.578 --> 04:50.790
may he live a life of spreading your word
and praise with joy.

04:51.666 --> 04:55.086
May sister Kyung-ja Kim's son, Oh-nam Ju,

04:55.169 --> 04:56.587
receive your love

04:56.671 --> 05:00.008
and be guided into the wonders
of the path you created for him.

05:00.091 --> 05:00.925
Amen.

05:03.428 --> 05:06.097
I don't know
if it's because God answered our prayers,

05:06.180 --> 05:08.725
but it turned out
my son's grades were good.

05:09.225 --> 05:12.061
Even though I couldn't send him
to a good private school.

05:12.562 --> 05:14.605
Hey, Oh-nam, are you studying?

05:15.106 --> 05:15.940
Yeah.

05:16.024 --> 05:19.277
Good. Study hard.
You're going to medical school, my son.

05:30.163 --> 05:32.623
C'mon, Mom,
I can do it myself.

05:33.624 --> 05:35.626
Hey, wait. Are you embarrassed?

05:35.710 --> 05:37.378
Hmm, baby?

05:37.920 --> 05:40.131
My son is… all grown up now.

05:40.214 --> 05:41.966
You're all grown up.

05:42.675 --> 05:43.968
My son got accepted

05:44.052 --> 05:46.929
into a four-year college in Seoul,
just like that.

05:47.013 --> 05:49.891
It wasn't medical school,
like I wanted, but still.

05:49.974 --> 05:51.726
Oh my God, my baby!

05:51.809 --> 05:53.686
Would you look at that!

05:53.770 --> 05:54.645
Oh, man!

05:54.729 --> 05:57.065
You look so handsome.
So, so handsome, right?

05:57.148 --> 05:58.566
-Don't you agree?
-Oh yes.

05:58.649 --> 06:00.526
-Mom!
-He looks so handsome.

06:02.987 --> 06:06.407
Then one day,
he suddenly wasn't my little boy anymore.

06:06.491 --> 06:07.742
Once he got a job.

06:07.825 --> 06:09.911
Is this the colonial era?!

06:10.453 --> 06:12.163
What do you mean, "independence"?

06:12.914 --> 06:13.831
Hey, listen.

06:14.332 --> 06:17.668
Just because you're earning money
doesn't mean you should waste it.

06:18.169 --> 06:21.130
You do know that
living by yourself's expensive, right?

06:22.548 --> 06:26.427
You're not getting married or anything,
I mean, why would you wanna move out?

06:27.053 --> 06:30.139
I just wanna live on my own.

06:35.812 --> 06:36.729
You're saying,

06:38.106 --> 06:39.565
you don't wanna live with me.

06:41.359 --> 06:43.111
That's not it, no.

06:43.694 --> 06:46.906
-It's just that I'm too far from work--
-"Far from work"? That's bullshit! C'mon!

06:46.989 --> 06:49.700
It takes me two hours to get there
and two hours to get home.

06:49.784 --> 06:51.077
That's--

06:52.120 --> 06:53.871
Listen, when I was raising you,

06:54.497 --> 06:58.501
I'd make my way to work through storms
or even typhoons, and I wouldn't complain.

06:59.001 --> 07:01.796
You, on the other hand…
Four hours, really?

07:02.672 --> 07:03.506
Oh my.

07:11.264 --> 07:14.851
I thought that if I put my foot down,
he'd change his mind.

07:16.018 --> 07:17.311
But he left anyway.

07:21.023 --> 07:22.358
Not only did he leave,

07:22.900 --> 07:25.445
he wouldn't even let me
anywhere near his house.

07:29.907 --> 07:33.161
Oh-nam, my son,
I made some side dishes for you.

07:33.244 --> 07:34.203
Are you home?

07:34.287 --> 07:36.414
Mom, I told you
I didn't need any.

07:36.497 --> 07:39.625
I don't even have time
to make food and eat at home these days.

07:39.709 --> 07:40.710
You little punk!

07:40.793 --> 07:42.211
Why are you like this, huh?

07:43.254 --> 07:46.382
What, do I have to beg you
to eat these side dishes, huh?

07:46.883 --> 07:49.051
This is not how I raised you, you get it?

07:49.135 --> 07:50.261
This-- This is just--

07:50.344 --> 07:53.097
Mom, it's not like that.
I'm eating well, and I'm just--

07:53.181 --> 07:55.391
Enough is enough, ungrateful jerk.

07:57.226 --> 07:58.311
Wait, you know what?

07:58.394 --> 08:00.813
You know what?
I'm never coming here ever again.

08:02.106 --> 08:05.067
This time, let's just
cut ties for good, Oh-nam!

08:05.151 --> 08:06.486
You… take care!

08:07.361 --> 08:08.988
Damn rascal. I--

08:09.780 --> 08:11.866
Damn it, damn it… Argh!

08:31.135 --> 08:33.137
MY SON ♥

08:41.270 --> 08:43.189
He only called once after that.

08:43.898 --> 08:46.651
OHNAM RESTAURANT

08:46.734 --> 08:49.737
Is that how you treat your mother?
You don't call me anymore?

08:51.280 --> 08:52.907
I missed the call, okay?

08:53.407 --> 08:55.535
Would it kill you to try calling me again?

08:57.370 --> 08:58.621
You know what? Forget it.

09:02.458 --> 09:03.793
Only one bottle today, okay?

09:12.385 --> 09:14.679
So frustrating.
This is too much, too much.

09:15.471 --> 09:16.681
That little punk.

09:17.598 --> 09:19.517
How will he find someone?

09:20.226 --> 09:21.561
Despite everything,

09:22.103 --> 09:25.773
I had faith he would come back to me
to be the good son I know he is.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.568
I never thought he would just disappear.

09:36.867 --> 09:38.828
-Here you go, ma'am.
-Thank you.

09:38.911 --> 09:41.664
-Thank you, sir.
-Oh-nam? Oh-nam!

09:42.164 --> 09:44.375
Oh!
What's that smell?

09:44.458 --> 09:47.670
What's that smell?
It smells rotten in here. Ugh!

09:49.505 --> 09:52.633
Okay,
this is the bathroom.

09:52.717 --> 09:54.176
Oh my God!

09:54.844 --> 09:56.554
Have a look at this place.

09:57.930 --> 09:58.848
Goodness.

09:59.765 --> 10:01.934
Oh my! That's scary, uh?

10:02.018 --> 10:03.769
Oh God, who is that?!

10:04.937 --> 10:05.938
Hey, who are you?

10:06.439 --> 10:09.025
It's a life-size doll.

10:09.900 --> 10:12.945
Is that… not a… a person?

10:13.696 --> 10:15.114
No, it's a doll.

10:15.823 --> 10:16.741
A doll?

10:17.408 --> 10:18.326
Yeah.

10:20.828 --> 10:22.246
Oh boy.

10:24.457 --> 10:25.416
What the hell?

10:26.834 --> 10:28.669
It looks so much like a human.

10:29.211 --> 10:30.921
That weird kid.

10:31.422 --> 10:33.633
Why would he have
a doll on his bed like th--

10:33.716 --> 10:35.217
Jesus, oh my goodness!

10:35.301 --> 10:36.594
Damn it.

10:36.677 --> 10:39.305
Huh? What's wrong?!

10:39.388 --> 10:40.222
What is it?

10:43.434 --> 10:45.186
Ugh!

10:45.269 --> 10:48.898
Why are you
so surprised? Huh?

10:55.196 --> 10:57.948
No! Not my son!

10:59.742 --> 11:01.202
Oh-nam!

11:01.952 --> 11:03.287
-My--
-No, don't touch it!

11:05.456 --> 11:07.750
Oh! Ma'am? Ma'am!

11:08.376 --> 11:10.378
Are you okay? Ma'am!

11:10.461 --> 11:11.587
Officer Park!

11:11.671 --> 11:13.339
Hey! Call an ambulance. Hurry!

11:13.422 --> 11:15.675
-Yes, sir!
-Ma'am! Are you okay?

11:15.758 --> 11:17.802
A dismembered body
has been found in the house

11:17.885 --> 11:20.680
of a recently missing
office worker, Oh-nam Ju.

11:20.763 --> 11:24.100
To identify the body,
an autopsy is being conducted.

11:24.767 --> 11:27.937
Police are currently
investigating Ju's whereabouts,

11:28.020 --> 11:30.398
who was last seen leaving work in October.

11:30.481 --> 11:33.609
And also trying to find a connection
between Ju and the victim.

11:34.568 --> 11:37.279
According to a police official,
the DNA analysis…

11:37.363 --> 11:38.406
Um, excuse me.

11:38.489 --> 11:41.325
Uh, which one of you is Ms. Kyung-ja Kim?

11:42.368 --> 11:45.579
…as they are investigating,
all possibilities are open.

11:45.663 --> 11:47.164
SEOUL YONGCHEON POLICE
YONG-JIN SEO / JONG-HUN CHOI

11:47.748 --> 11:50.042
What are you saying right now?

11:50.918 --> 11:53.796
-It's not my son?!
-Correct.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.883
Oh my God!

11:57.967 --> 12:01.095
Oh my God. It's not my son,
they're saying it's not my son.

12:01.178 --> 12:03.305
-It's not my son!
-That's wonderful news.

12:03.389 --> 12:05.141
-I'm so glad.
-Then who--

12:05.224 --> 12:07.393
Who was in that, uh, black bag?

12:07.476 --> 12:10.604
Well, at this moment,
we don't have enough to identify him.

12:10.688 --> 12:12.148
We just know it's a man.

12:12.231 --> 12:14.358
Well, that's fine.

12:14.442 --> 12:16.318
As long as it's not my son.

12:16.402 --> 12:17.528
Oh my God!

12:17.611 --> 12:19.405
Oh, oh!

12:20.072 --> 12:22.658
Uh, can, uh, can--
can you get me some water?

12:23.200 --> 12:24.034
Water.

12:26.662 --> 12:28.622
So, um, ma'am…

12:30.374 --> 12:33.294
when was the, uh,
last time you talked to your son,

12:34.170 --> 12:35.004
by the way?

12:35.087 --> 12:38.716
About two weeks ago.

12:38.799 --> 12:39.800
Take notes.

12:39.884 --> 12:41.051
On my birthday.

12:41.135 --> 12:42.678
-Oh.
-"Birthday."

12:42.762 --> 12:46.557
Um, did your son
have problems with anybody, by chance?

12:46.640 --> 12:48.559
Problems? What problems?

12:48.642 --> 12:51.395
He always got along
with his co-workers and everyone.

12:53.689 --> 12:54.607
Wait.

12:55.191 --> 12:56.817
Why are you asking me about him?

12:58.944 --> 13:00.446
Oh, well…

13:02.907 --> 13:03.741
What is it?

13:05.075 --> 13:06.035
Do you think

13:06.619 --> 13:08.829
my son killed that man?
Is that what you think?!

13:08.913 --> 13:12.208
Well, ma'am, there's a chance he did,
there's a chance he didn't.

13:12.291 --> 13:14.668
-We just--
-You're fucking kidding me, c'mon!

13:14.752 --> 13:16.712
My son's not the kind of person
to hurt anyone!

13:16.796 --> 13:19.548
He pretty much faints
at the sight of blood!

13:19.632 --> 13:22.676
How the hell
could you even think he'd kill someone?

13:22.760 --> 13:25.012
Get lost, you jerks!

13:25.095 --> 13:28.432
Later that day,
the police went to Oh-nam's workplace.

13:28.516 --> 13:32.186
So I can't think of anyone
who was noticeably, uh,

13:32.269 --> 13:34.480
or particularly close to Mr. Ju.

13:34.980 --> 13:37.525
If there's anything I can say about him,

13:38.192 --> 13:41.529
it's that, uh, when, um,
things didn't go his way,

13:41.612 --> 13:43.405
he'd blow up, all of a sudden.

13:43.489 --> 13:47.159
So that would, uh,
startle me every once in a while.

13:47.243 --> 13:49.787
The last time I saw him
was when Mo-mi Kim quit.

13:49.870 --> 13:52.623
He came to me
to get her address to deliver her things.

13:52.706 --> 13:55.543
-Why did Ms. Mo-mi Kim quit?
-I don't really know.

13:56.752 --> 13:58.921
She gave me
her resignation letter out of nowhere.

13:59.421 --> 14:01.715
You're asking me if Mr. Ju liked Mo-mi?

14:02.675 --> 14:05.469
Uh, you know what, I'm not really sure.

14:05.553 --> 14:07.596
He wasn't a man of many words, you know?

14:08.222 --> 14:10.057
Mo-mi did say something once.

14:10.891 --> 14:14.353
Something like, how she felt
Mr. Ju was keeping an eye on her.

14:14.979 --> 14:17.648
However,
I thought she was overreacting.

14:18.190 --> 14:20.568
She does, um, overreact often, you know?

14:25.322 --> 14:28.158
Oh dear, the things I go through.
Come on in.

14:28.242 --> 14:30.953
The police searched Mo-mi Kim's place too.

14:31.036 --> 14:33.163
She threw everything away before she left.

14:33.247 --> 14:35.374
She said she was
going abroad or something.

14:37.418 --> 14:39.920
Was there anything
unusual about her when she left?

14:40.713 --> 14:42.423
-Unusual?
-Yeah.

14:45.426 --> 14:48.971
Oh. Uh, she looked like
she got plastic surgery.

14:49.471 --> 14:50.472
Plastic surgery?

14:50.556 --> 14:53.267
Yeah. I mean,
you know how after plastic surgery,

14:53.350 --> 14:55.686
they wrap the person's face
with white gauze?

14:55.769 --> 14:57.062
Her face was like that.

14:57.146 --> 14:59.732
At first I thought
someone beat her up or something,

14:59.815 --> 15:01.233
I was thrown off, you know?

15:03.611 --> 15:04.528
Was she

15:05.446 --> 15:06.780
with a man, by any chance?

15:07.281 --> 15:08.115
A man?

15:09.283 --> 15:10.910
No. She lived alone.

15:10.993 --> 15:13.871
I mean, did she ever come home
with a man before?

15:13.954 --> 15:16.332
Nah, never, she never did.

15:16.415 --> 15:19.001
Every once in a while
she'd put on really loud music

15:19.084 --> 15:22.087
and sing and dance like crazy,
but nothing else.

15:24.089 --> 15:26.634
All right. Thanks a lot.

15:27.801 --> 15:29.929
-Are you done?
-Yes, we're done.

15:30.012 --> 15:32.598
The police thought
that my Oh-nam and that girl

15:32.681 --> 15:34.558
had run off somewhere together.

15:35.559 --> 15:37.686
We have received information

15:37.770 --> 15:40.397
that a colleague of Oh-nam Ju's
disappeared as well.

15:40.481 --> 15:42.858
On the same night he went missing himself.

15:43.484 --> 15:47.196
We went to her hometown,
Daesan, and tried to talk with her family.

15:47.279 --> 15:50.783
Excuse me, when did you last speak
with Ms. Mo-mi Kim, your daughter?

15:52.034 --> 15:55.371
The corpse was found
in a studio in Yongcheon-gu,

15:55.871 --> 15:57.957
the home of the missing Oh-nam Ju.

15:58.999 --> 16:03.462
There were over 2,000 illegal adult videos
saved on his computer.

16:03.963 --> 16:08.342
A sex doll, as well as several adult toys,
were found at the scene of the crime.

16:09.009 --> 16:11.387
His apartment was filled
with pornographic toys,

16:11.470 --> 16:14.431
and that could point
to psychological issues.

16:14.515 --> 16:16.600
Chances are his perception of sex
was abnormal.

16:17.226 --> 16:20.479
The problem here is that the expression
of his desire

16:20.562 --> 16:22.356
would become twisted

16:22.439 --> 16:24.984
and found in the form
of stalking and obsession.

16:26.860 --> 16:30.322
Hey, you piece of shit.
I told you to find my son,

16:30.406 --> 16:34.118
but instead, you make him out
to be a pervert, stalker, and murderer?!

16:35.452 --> 16:38.956
I should just shred all of you bastards
to pieces or something!

16:39.039 --> 16:41.667
My son is a gentleman! He's a good person!

16:42.626 --> 16:44.211
There's no fucking way

16:44.294 --> 16:46.880
my baby did such a thing, you fuckers!

16:46.964 --> 16:48.841
Damn you, bastards!

16:48.924 --> 16:50.175
That's when I decided

16:51.051 --> 16:52.886
that I have to find my son myself.

16:52.970 --> 16:55.222
NEW BEGINNING

17:00.352 --> 17:01.437
Does it work now?

17:01.937 --> 17:03.105
Uh-- Yes.

17:03.731 --> 17:04.690
Thank you, mister.

17:08.777 --> 17:10.696
Hello. What's this?

17:18.287 --> 17:19.663
Uh, and what's this?

17:22.458 --> 17:24.626
Where'd the pointer go? Huh?

17:26.462 --> 17:27.379
Oh, damn it.

17:28.422 --> 17:29.965
What the heck is all of this?

17:30.049 --> 17:33.510
If I wanted to find my son,
I needed to know more about him.

17:33.594 --> 17:35.512
So I started taking computer lessons.

17:35.596 --> 17:39.058
Typing is one of the basics
of learning how to use a computer.

17:39.141 --> 17:41.810
It's not easy
typing with both hands right off the bat,

17:41.894 --> 17:44.271
so you'll learn to type
with each hand separat--

17:44.354 --> 17:48.567
If you're having a hard time with it,
I would recommend practicing at home.

17:48.650 --> 17:52.321
Today, we're going to look
at the basics of browsing the Internet.

17:52.404 --> 17:54.573
If you look at the desktop screen,
there should be--

17:54.656 --> 17:56.742
Today, we'll learn how to send an email.

17:56.825 --> 18:00.621
So an email is basically like
a home address to receive electronic mail.

18:00.704 --> 18:02.122
Your online home address!

18:03.540 --> 18:05.542
MASK GIRL

18:05.626 --> 18:07.628
FAN CAFÉ FOR MASK GIRL LOVERS

18:10.923 --> 18:15.385
If I wanted to find my son,
I had to learn more about that girl.

18:15.469 --> 18:17.888
HOT POST
UNANSWERED QUESTIONS ABOUT MASK GIRL

18:21.433 --> 18:23.185
HER REAL NAME IS MO-MI KIM
DAEHAN INSURANCE

18:23.268 --> 18:24.561
Mo-mi Kim.

18:25.312 --> 18:26.522
MASK GIRL AT A COMPANY DINNER

